# migrated from tests/cases/reflexive_skeleton.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test reflexive_skeleton]
# gen166 (E1 reflexive): introspection closed to execution. Asked to SHOW the
# dialogue (not just describe the method), parrot0 emits a runnable, single-line
# `>`-turn skeleton built from the parts it derives from its own module(X)
# self-model. The emitted turns really compose — see
# tests/compose/skeleton_proposed_en.dlg, which runs exactly this spine. It still
# only proposes; an external agent fills the names, runs it, and commits.
> show me the dialogue you would run to prove your parts compose
< Here is a held-out dialogue I would run (fresh names; an external agent fills and runs it, I do not): > every brave knight is a hero > aldric is a knight > is aldric a hero? > why isn't aldric a hero? > aldric is brave > how robust is that conclusion?
